SIMPLE: prig
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prig
<hw>Prig</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Prigged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prigging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[A modification of
<ets>prick</ets>.]</ety> <def>To haggle about the price of a commodity;
to bargain hard.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prig
<hw>Prig</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cheapen.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Perhaps orig., to ride off with. See
<er>Prick</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To filch or steal; <as>as,
to <ex>prig</ex> a handkerchief</as>.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prig
<hw>Prig</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pert, conceited,
pragmatical fellow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The queer <qex>prig</qex> of a doctor.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thief; a filcher.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Priggery</ent>⟦br⟧
